- --------------------------------------------------------------------------
CONECTIVA LINUX SECURITY ANNOUNCEMENT 
- --------------------------------------------------------------------------

PACKAGE   : apache
SUMMARY   : Fix for mod_ssl vulnerability
DATE      : 2004-11-04 12:47:00
ID        : CLA-2004:885
RELEVANT
RELEASES  : 9, 10

- -------------------------------------------------------------------------

DESCRIPTION
 Apache[1] is the most popular webserver in use today.
 
 An issue[2] in the mod_ssl module was reported[3] by Hartmut Keil.
 When a particular location is configured to require a specific set of
 cipher suites through the "SSLCipherSuite" directive in its directory
 or location context, a client could be able to access that location
 using any cipher suite allowed by the virtual host configuration.


SOLUTION
 It is recommended that all Apache users upgrade their packages.
 
 
 REFERENCES
 1.http://apache.httpd.org/
 2.http://cve.mitre.org/cgi-bin/cvename.cgi?name=CAN-2004-0885
 3.http://issues.apache.org/bugzilla/show_bug.cgi?id=31505


